  "prompt": "What can I do to feel better about myself?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions to help improve your self-esteem and feel better about yourself:\n\n1. Practice self-compassion\n- Be kind to yourself\n- Avoid negative self-talk\n- Treat yourself like you would a good friend\n\n2. Set and achieve small goals\n- Create achievable daily or weekly objectives\n- Celebrate your accomplishments\n- Build confidence through consistent progress\n\n3. Exercise and take care of your physical health\n- Regular physical activity boosts mood\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Get enough sleep\n\n4. Develop new skills\n- Learn something new\n- Take a class or online course\n- Challenge yourself\n\n5. Practice positive affirmations\n- Use encouraging self-statements\n- Focus on your strengths\n- Replace negative thoughts with positive ones\n\n6. Surround yourself with supportive people\n- Spend time with those who uplift you\n- Limit interactions with negative influences\n- Build healthy relationships\n\n7. Engage in activities you enjoy\n- Pursue hobbies\n- Do things that make you happy\n- Express creativity\n\n8. Consider professional help\n- Talk to a therapist\n- Work on underlying self-esteem issues\n- Learn coping strategies\n\nRemember, building self-esteem is a process that takes time and consistent effort.",
